post_text: Congratulations to Damyn Rother on being selected as a 2020 Salvation Army D.J.‚Äôs Hero!
shared_text:
The Salvation Army of Omaha
May 26 at 3:00 PM ¬∑

Damyn Rother, of Greeley, suffered much heartbreak in the wake of his older brother‚Äôs suicide and the deaths of his beloved grandparents. Amid his grief, he was also diagnosed with severe Crohn‚Äôs disease. Rather than turning inward, however, Damyn focused on serving others by founding a teen support network at his church, engaging in community service, excelling in athletics and launching an annual run/walk in memory of his brother, which to date has funded eight scholarships. Damyn plans to major in business management at Wayne State College. #2020DJsHero

Learn more about Damyn here: https://tinyurl.com/ybm27jt6

post_text:
NSAA State Wrestling Update:

Both Central Valley Wrestlers advance to Saturday medal rounds! Shaye Wood defeated Connor Wells of Anselmo-Merna 4-0 in his Semifinal match, he will move on to wrestle for the 126lb State Championship tomorrow afternoon against Gavin Schernikau of Centennial! Enrique Martinez defeated Dennis Vogl of Crawford in the 3rd Round Consolations, and will move on to the Consolation Semifinals tomorrow morning against Dustin Klingsporn of Axtel!
text:
NSAA State Wrestling Update:

Both Central Valley Wrestlers advance to Saturday medal rounds! Shaye Wood defeated Connor Wells of Anselmo-Merna 4-0 in his Semifinal match, he will move on to wrestle for the 126lb State Championship tomorrow afternoon against Gavin Schernikau of Centennial! Enrique Martinez defeated Dennis Vogl of Crawford in the 3rd Round Consolations, and will move on to the Consolation Semifinals tomorrow morning against Dustin Klingsporn of Axtel!

post_text:
NSAA State Wrestling Update:

Shaye Wood went 2-0 on Thursday pinning Sam Tourney of Shelton in Round 1 and then beat Brenner McLaughlin of Thayer Central in the Quarterfinals 11-0. Shaye will wrestle Connor Wells of Anselmo-Merna in the Semi-Finals tonight.

Enrique Martinez went 1-1 on Thursday pinning Cody Lambert of Southern Valley in Round 1 and then was defeated by Nate Christensen of Plainview in the Quarterfinals, 4-0. Enrique won his first match in the 2nd Round Consolations Friday by a score of 8-0 over Luke Honstein of Hemingford. He will wrestle again tonight in the 3rd Round Consolations against Dennis Vogl of Crawford.
